data.enText: that can be said to be true in the case of sb/sth
Much of the form was not applicable (= did not apply) to me.
data.chText: 表格中很多部分不适用于我。

data.enText: Give details of children where applicable (= if you have any) .
The new approach had wide applicability to all sorts of different problems.
data.chText: 新方法广泛适用于解决各种各样的问题。

simple_means.memory_skill: ap- 朝,向 + lic 准许 + -able 可...的

example: gave applicable examples to support her argument

example.ex: What is a reasonable standard for one family is not applicable for another...
example.tran: 对一个家庭合理的标准并不适用于另一个家庭。

example.ex: Appraisal has traditionally been seen as most applicable to those in management and supervisory positions...
example.tran: 传统上认为业绩评定最适用于那些身处管理和监督职位之人。

example.ex: It should include a review of energy usage and, where applicable, the production and disposal of waste.
example.tran: 它应该包括对能耗的检查结果，适当时还应包括对垃圾的产生和处理的审查结果。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>to</l> n

value.def: Something that is applicable to a particular situation is relevant to it or can be applied to it.
value.tran: 适用的；适当的；可实施的

example.ex: Piaget himself wrote relatively little about the applicability of his theories to education.
example.tran: 皮亚热本人就其理论对教育的适用性论述相对很少。
